app.containers.App.entities.taxonomies.1: No human rights body assigned yet

Different UN human rights monitoring mechanisms exist that provide recommendations to States. These are Charter-based bodies, including the Universal Periodic Review (UPR) and Special Procedures, Treaty bodies, created under the international human rights treaties, as well as regional human rights mechanisms.
app.containers.App.entities.taxonomies.2: Reporting cycles of the different human rights bodies.
app.containers.App.entities.taxonomies.3: No human rights issue assigned yet
Human rights issues according to the Universal Human Rights Index's classification system for recommendations (also called themes).
app.containers.App.entities.taxonomies.4: Affected persons according to the Universal Human Rights Index's classification system for recommendations.
app.containers.App.entities.taxonomies.5: Thematic clusters are country specific themes used to better manage and group recommendations according to national priorities.
app.containers.App.entities.taxonomies.6: Government organisations responsible for implementing government actions
app.containers.App.entities.taxonomies.7: The Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) are a universal call to action to end poverty, protect the planet and ensure that all people enjoy peace and prosperity.
app.containers.App.entities.taxonomies.8: The progress status at last update of all the actions the government has committed to.
